---
@META
dir: src/app/api/auth
updated: 2026-03-18
files: 0
stack: Next.js 14, NextAuth 4, bcryptjs

@EXPORTS
[...nextauth]/route.ts: NextAuthHandlers — GET/POST handlers for NextAuth (signin, signout, session, csrf)
register/route.ts: RegisterHandler — POST handler for user registration

@PROCESSES
Login: POST credentials → bcrypt compare → JWT token → session cookie
Register: POST {name,email,username,password} → validate → bcrypt hash → prisma.user.create → return user
OAuth: Google|GitHub provider → PrismaAdapter → create/link account → JWT

@FUNCTIONS
POST_register(request) → NextResponse
  purpose: create new user with hashed password
  side-effects: db (User create)
  called-by: /auth/signup page, /onboarding flow

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: @/lib/auth (authOptions), @/lib/prisma, @/lib/validations
external: next-auth, bcryptjs

@WARNINGS
- Credentials provider uses JWT strategy (not database sessions)
- OAuth providers conditionally loaded based on env vars
---
